steps:
  - peel
  - cut wedges
  - soak and rinse
  - boil for 6 mins with big pinch of salt and splash of rice wine vinegar (instead of baking soda) to keep some structure
  - strain then pour boiled wedges into cornstarch slurry and stir with fork to crunch edges
  - cover with peanut oil
components:
  - name: oven bake
    steps:
      - bake at 240°C for 15 mins per side until crisp
      - add more oil at halfway flip if dry
  - name: deep fry
    steps:
      - deep fry in peanut oil at 180°C for 50s
      - dry
      - fry again for 3.5 mins
  - name: spice mix (for 1 big sweet potato)
    ingredients:
      - item: paprika
        mass: 1
      - item: garlic powder
        mass: 2
      - item: salt
        mass: 2
    steps:
      - make spice mix and coat in a bowl
notes: |
  Cornstarch slurry ratio is 50g starch : 80g cold water.
